The paper discusses capacity gains and cooperation strategies in a relay network, which are topics typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) subfields. The use of channel state information (CSI) and power allocation are also important aspects of communication systems, which could place the paper in the systems and control (cs.SY) subfield. Additionally, the paper mentions fast Rayleigh fading, which is a common model in wireless communications and could relate to the multimedia (cs.MM) subfield. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of cooperative schemes, which could also be relevant to the computer networks (cs.COM) subfield.
